headline.main: FLIER LANDS PLANE WITH 180 FLAK HOLES; Third of Wing Blown Off in Foray Over Tunisia

lead_paragraph: AN ADVANCED AMERICAN AIR BASE, in North Africa, Feb. 27 (AP) -- With 180 flak holes in his plane, and both gunners wounded, Lieutenant Dave Bensley, 24 years old, of Alden, N.Y., flew his crippled A-20 low-flying bomber back to its base and a perfect belly-skid landing after strafing forty Axis trucks and other targets.
abstract: Lt Bensley flies plane with 180 flak holes back to air base
